andhian technique. It explores, in terms familiar to the Western reader, its distinguishing characteristics and its far-reaching implications for social and political philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aConflict management. 0aNonviolence. 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / General.2bisacsh  aBhagavad Gita.  aCarlyle, Thomas.  aChristianity.  aGandhian dialectic.  aGandhian revolution.  aHegel.  aMahabharata.  aPathans.  aPlato.  aPyarelal.  aQuaker method.  aRama Raj.  aSarabhai, Ambalal.  aTagore, Rabindranath.  aagreement.  aaparigraha.  aatheism.  abread-labor.  aconscience.  adeath.  ademonstrations.  adharma.  adisobedience.  aeconomic equality.  afreedom.  ahistoricism.  aidealism.  ain anarchism.  ainjury.  ajail-going.  aleadership.  amass meetings.  amasses.  ametaphysics.  aon the dialectic.  aontology.  aorganismic theory.  apower.  asocial structure.  auntouchability.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691218045zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691218045423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691218045.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK